{
  "verses": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Do Not Envy"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Saying 20"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Do not envy wicked menor desire their company;"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "for their hearts devise violence, and their lips declare trouble."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Saying 21"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "By wisdom a house is built and by understanding it is established;"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "through knowledge its rooms are filledwith every precious and beautiful treasure."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Saying 22"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "A wise man is strong,[^67] and a man of knowledge enhances his strength."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Only with sound guidance should you wage war, and victory lies in a multitude of counselors."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Saying 23"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Wisdom is too high for a fool; he does not open his mouth in the meeting place."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Saying 24"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He who plots evilwill be called a schemer."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "A foolish scheme is sin, and a mocker is detestable to men."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Saying 25"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "If you faint in the day of distress, how small is your strength!"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "11",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Rescue those being led away to death, and restrain those stumbling toward the slaughter."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "12",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "If you say,"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Behold, we did not know about this,",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "does not He who weighs hearts consider it? Does not the One who guards your life know? Will He not repay a man according to his deeds?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Saying 26"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "13",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Eat honey, my son, for it is good, and the honeycomb is sweet to your taste."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "14",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Know therefore that wisdom is sweet to your soul. If you find it, there is a future for you,\nand your hope will never be cut off."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Saying 27"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "15",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Do not lie in wait, O wicked man, near the dwelling of the righteous; do not destroy his resting place."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "16",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "For though a righteous man may fall seven times, he still gets up; but the wicked stumble in bad times."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Saying 28"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "17",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Do not gloat when your enemy falls, and do not let your heart rejoice when he stumbles,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "18",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "or the LORD will see and disapprove, and turn His wrath away from him."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Saying 29"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "19",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Do not fret over evildoers, and do not be envious of the wicked."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "20",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "For the evil man has no future; the lamp of the wicked will be extinguished."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Saying 30"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "21",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "My son, fear the LORD and the king, and do not associate with the rebellious."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "22",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "For they will bring sudden destruction. Who knows what ruin they can bring?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Further Sayings of the Wise"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "23",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "These also are sayings of the wise: To show partiality in judgmentis not good."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "24",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Whoever tells the guilty,"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "You are innocent",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "—peoples will curse him, and nations will denounce him;"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "25",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "but it will go well with those who convict the guilty, and rich blessing will come upon them."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "26",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "An honest answer givenis like a kiss on the lips."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "27",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Complete your outdoor work and prepare your field; after that, you may build your house."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "28",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Do not testify against your neighbor without cause, and do not deceive with your lips."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "29",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Do not say,"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "I will do to him as he has done to me; I will repay the man according to his work.",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "30",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "I went past the field of a slacker and by the vineyard of a man lacking judgment."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "31",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Thorns had grown up everywhere, thistles had covered the ground,\nand the stone wall was broken down."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "32",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "I observed and took it to heart; I looked and received instruction:"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "33",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "A little sleep, a little slumber, a little folding of the hands to rest,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "34",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and poverty will come upon you like a robber, and need like a bandit."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}